    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="23"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851<gloss target="#t_G1">G</gloss>.01/5–749:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-07T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 7, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1862. While Embassy has not received copy Department’s 70, May 2, to Saigon,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d23fn1">The Department repeated telegram 70 in telegram 1522,
                        May 10, 8 p. m., to Paris.</note> I wish to state my concurrence in general
                    line contained latter’s 1412 [<hi rend="italic">141</hi>], May 6, to
                        Department.<note n="2" xml:id="d23fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In connection with Abbott’s recommendation for “immediate and continued pressure”
                    (Paragraph 4–<hi rend="italic">a</hi>), in which I expressly concur, I suggest
                    that in immediate stage it would be helpful, in event Embassy is to undertake
                    such representations, if they could be accompanied by indications our intentions
                    according <hi rend="italic">b</hi>, <hi rend="italic">c</hi>, and possible <hi
                        rend="italic">d</hi>, same paragraph, provided representations are
                    successful.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 1862 (for action); repeated Saigon 73 (for information).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
